snippet.textDisplay:
MOTHER SONG

Tu zariya, Hoon main zariya,
Aur uski kitpaa dariya dariya,
Hain jo ankhiya nirmal, 
Duniya nirmal, 
Chhalka chhalka, chhal chhal chhal chhal

You are the medium, So am I, 
and his (Our God) kindness is vast (large/huge) than a ocean.
If your eyes are serene (Calm / Peaceful)
the world itself will seem serene,

Ho zubaan koi bhi, 
Bol dil se tu bol,
Ya misri si ho, 
Ya shahad si ho.

(To all) Our languages might be any, 
but use kind words that comes straight from the heart,
it will be sweet as sugar, sweet as honey.

Anti al umm,
Anti il hayaa, 
Anti alhob,
Antilee alduna, anti lee aldunya.

You are the mother
You are the life
You are love, 
You are the world to me, you are the world to me

Reedaha Reedaha, 
Kefima reedaha, 
Teflatan ya halee, 
Wil asaal reegaha. 

(Mother) I love her, I love her, 
However it may be, I love her, 
She looks beautiful (perfect/nice), for me, 
In her voice there is honey.

snippet.textDisplay: Wow.... Jordanian, Indian and Nepali/ Tibetan fusion but Ani Choying looks misplaced as a nun here.... Not that she shouldn't be involved in music but it is a bit too frivolous for a monk to be in this set-up...nevertheless her prayers are a blessing for my Nephew. My sister heard her prayers to calm herself and the boy turned out so well! He is a genius and started crawling at 2 months! He can already walk at 8 months and surf the smart phone and articulate by gestures and sound more clearly than his peers! LOL.... Funny thing is we are not even Buddhist or Nepali but Christians from Arunachal! LOL...
